 Tradipitant, 85mg b.i.d., does not significantly affect gastric motor functions (GV or GE). Importantly, there was no retardation of GE by tradipitant, which is important in relation to its potential use in patients with gastroparesis. Clinic trials registry ClinicalTrials.gov #NCT04849559.
